I18nJs
=======

I18nJs converts all your translations into JavaScript so you can use them on
the client side. It mimicks the Ruby I18n API and works in pretty much the
same way:

//JavaScript
I18n.defaultLocale // "en"
I18n.locale // Whatever the locale has been set to on the server

I18n.t('hello') // "Hello World"
I18n.t('messages.invalid', {scope:['activerecord', 'errors']})  // "is invalid"
I18n.t('activerecord.errors.template.header', {count:4, model:'horse'}) // "4 errors prohibited this horse from being saved"


Example
=======

I18n.defaultLocale // => "en"
I18n.t('invalid', {scope:'activerecord.errors.messages', count:5})
=> "must be equal to 5"


